    "ivr_number": "5165183",
    "permit_type": "Land Use ReviewType 2 procedureRP - Replat",
    "work_description": "A replat can be used to remove or reconfigure lot lines within a site to combine existing units of land into no more than three parcels. The subject site consists of three existing lots described as BLOCK 14&15 TL 11100, PARKROSE & RPLT; BLOCK 16 E 1/2 OF LOT B, PARKROSE & RPLT; BLOCK 16 W 1/2 OF LOT B, PARKROSE & RPLT. The applicant is proposing to replat the subject site into three reconfigured parcels. Parcel 1 is proposed to be 174,208 square feet and will contain existing apartment buildings, parking areas, and garages. Parcel 2 is proposed to be reduced in size to 7,800 square feet and will contain one existing house and garage to remain. Parcel 3 is proposed to be reduced in size to 7,844 square feet and will contain one existing house and garage to remain. The applicant is also proposing an Adjustment to the asphalt paving limitation. The sum of the existing asphalt paving on the three lots meets the 15% limitation but the area of asphalt on Parcel 1 will increase from the existing 22% to 25% with the transfer of the parking and detached garages from Parcels 2 and 3 to Parcel 1 through the replat. Zoning Code Section 33.266.130.C.4.a(2) has a maximum asphalt paving allowance on a site of 15%. The applicant requests an Adjustment to increase this percentage on Parcel 1.",
